library.title: Robot Alchemic Drive: Part 1 (WAYNE'S GRAND TOUR)
library.description:
It is cheaper to buy vegetables here. many moons ago i saw the name of a game in the PS2 library while looking for Grand Tour games to explore... Robot Alchemic Drive. i was intrigued by the little I saw of it, but thought it looked too involved for a multi-game showcase. over the years a few clips of it would spread on the websites and would leave an impact on me that hasn't left. and i decided. i MUST play this game. and holy Shit was i right: i needed to play this. and you need to see it. come along for the ROBOT ALCHEMIC DRIVE GRAND TOUR

library.title: Robot Alchemic Drive: Part 4 - Grandpa's Awesome Idea (WAYNE'S GRAND TOUR)
library.description:
Sometimes Grandpa has an idea so awesome and cool you just have to kill everyone. RAD is back in our penultimate journey through its wonderful world of a city and a field of grass. This time with a special feature: a direct illegal line into the Civilization Preservation Foundation's comm lines. Meaning we get EXTRA rare dialogue that for some reason happens when the chat gives bits... we were very mad that this chunk had very little Natural Nanao but she showed up anyways thanks to our illegal surveillance :D

library.author: wayneradiotv ON DEMAND
library.title: Robot Alchemic Drive: FINALE - Wiltz Takin' Over, Goodbye Senjo (WAYNE'S GRAND TOUR)
library.description:
Chairman! We have become one mind and body!!- at long last. Robot Alchemic Drive draws to a close. its a bittersweet goodbye but i wanted to make it as special as possible: so we made sure to make it a BIG send-off. we begin our celebration with the live creation of REAL BREAD & WATER SOUP (Nanao's Favorite) to fuel our final stretch, then we BEAT DA GAME with finalized frequency hacking interactivity, and play the multiplayer mode for a few minutes... and we look at male 2 a little bit. GOODBYE SENJO! GOODBYE NANAO! GOODBYE WILTZ! GOODBYE YUI! GOODBYE THERMAL CANNON SOLDIER!

library.title: After 20+ Years, I Finish Donkey Kong 64 (DONKEY KONG 64 PART 5, THE FINALE!!)
library.description:
Donkey Kong 64 held a confusing place in my heart. I wanted to love it as a kid but it seemed so complex and huge. The levels confused me and I was just completely lost... I eventually gave up and never played it again. Until NOW!! We began this journey late last year and now we FINISH THE STORY. It is time to beat DONKEY KONG 64!!!!!!!!!!!
